{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"oe485i4et1p69145l89f6zi","title":"Langchain","desc":"","updated":1766727093332,"created":1766727093332,"custom":{},"fname":"learning.langchain","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Harshita-notes","sync":"sync"},"contentHash":"3a5dfdb5b94ebd03a0dd523e23bdfbe5","links":[],"anchors":{"common-components-of-langchain":{"type":"header","text":"Common components of Langchain","value":"common-components-of-langchain","line":13,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"trkx8xrg7g2fm023ez4ldqj","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"langchain\">Langchain<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#langchain\"></a></h1>\n<ul>\n<li>open source development framework for LLM applications.</li>\n<li>two packages: python and JS(TS)</li>\n<li>key value adds:\n<ul>\n<li>modular components</li>\n<li>uses cases: common ways to combine components.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"common-components-of-langchain\">Common components of Langchain<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#common-components-of-langchain\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Models</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Prompts</strong>: how to get models to do the work</li>\n<li><strong>Indexes</strong>: ways of ingesting data so that you can combine it with model</li>\n<li><strong>Chains</strong>: end to end use cases.</li>\n<li><strong>Agents</strong>: a endtime use case which uses the model as reasoning engine.</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"dlb5bmx7v8f6otsgongz4vx","title":"Hi","desc":"","updated":1663067414354,"created":1648190029829,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Harshita-notes","sync":"sync"},"contentHash":"5e58da66991a53ed4cf17d0cade77fe6","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"dlb5bmx7v8f6otsgongz4vx","vaultName":"Harshita-notes"},"value":"user.tharshita13","alias":"@tharshita13","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column